                        "text": "\"This definitely looks like steam coming out when you lift the lid of a pot of boiling soup\ud83d\ude0a\nCan you imagine these earthen buildings (Tulou \u571f\u697c) built by the ethnic Hakka and Minnan people of rural Fujian Province dates back to 700 years and were once mistaken for missile silos by American officials poring over satellite images? They have been inscribed as one of the 46 Fujian Tulou World Heritage Sites \ud83c\udde8\ud83c\uddf3.\u2800\u2800\nThe locals call these Tulou [\u56db\u83dc\u4e00\u6c64] \"four dishes and one soup\u201d as the layout looks like a typical dinner setting of four plates and soup in the center.\"\nTag someone who must see this!\n\u2014\n\ud83d\udccd #DiscoverChina\n\u2014\n\ud83d\udcf8 Photo and caption taken by @luxplush"
                    }
                }
            ]
